      div.span9
        section#global
          div.page-header
            h1 Global styles
          h2 Requires HTML5 doctype
          p teambition UI makes use of certain HTML elements and CSS
            | properties that require the use of the HTML5 doctype.
            | Include it at the beginning of all your projects.
          pre.prettyprint.
            | &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
            | &lt;html&gt;
            | ...
            | &lt;/html&gt;
          h2 Typography and links
          p teambition UI sets basic global display, typography, and link
            |styles. Specifically, we:
          ul
            li Remove
              code margin
              | &nbsp;on the body
            li Set
              code background-color: white;
              | &nbsp;on the
              code body
            li Use the
              code @baseFontFamily
              | &nbsp;,
              code @baseFontSize
              | &nbsp;, and
              code @baseLineHeight
              | &nbsp;attributes as our typographic base
            li Set the global link color via
              code @linkColor
              | &nbsp;and apply link underlines only on
              code :hover
          p These styles can be found within
            strong scaffolding.less

        section#gridSystem
          div.page-header
            h1 Grid system
          h2 Live grid example
          p The default teambition UI grid system utilizes
            strong 12 columns
            | , making for a 940px wide container without
            a(href="./scaffolding.html#responsive") responsive features
            | enabled. With the responsive CSS file added, the grid adapts
            | to be 724px and 1170px wide depending on your viewport.
            | Below 767px viewports, the columns become fluid and stack
            | vertically.
          div.bs-docs-grid
            div.row.show-grid
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
            div.row.show-grid
              div.span2 2
              div.span3 3
              div.span3 3
            div.row.show-grid
              div.span4 4
              div.span4 4
            div.row.show-grid
              div.span8 8
          h2 Basic grid HTML
          p For a simple two column layout, create a
            code .row
            | &nbps;and add the appropriate number of&nbsp;
            code .span*
            | &nbsp;columns. As this is a 12-column grid, each&nbsp;
            code .span*
            | &nbsp;spans a number of those 12 columns, and should always
            | add up to 12 for each row (or the number of columns in the
            | parent).
          pre.prettyprint.
            | &lt;div class="row"&gt;
            | &lt;div class="span4"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
            | &lt;div class="span8"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
            | &lt;/div&gt;
          p Given this example, we have
            code .span4
            | &nbsp;and&nbsp;
            code .span8
            | &nbsp;making for 12 total columns and a complete row.
          h2 Offsetting columns
          p Move columns to the right using <code>.offset*</code> classes. Each class increases the left margin of a column by a whole column. For example, <code>.offset4</code> moves <code>.span4</code> over four columns.</p>
          div.bs-docs-grid
            div.row.show-grid
              div.span4 4
              div.span3.offset1 3 offset 1
            div.row.show-grid
              div.span3.offset1 3 offset 1
              div.span3.offset1 3 offset 1
            div.row.show-grid
              div.span5.offset3 6 offset 2
          pre.prettyprint.
            | &lt;div class="row"&gt;
            | &lt;div class="span4"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
            | &lt;div class="span3 offset1"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
            | &lt;/div&gt;

          h2 Nesting columns
          p To nest your content with the default grid, add a new <code>.row</code> and set of <code>.span*</code> columns within an existing <code>.span*</code> column. Nested rows should include a set of columns that add up to the number of columns of its parent.</p>
          div.row.show-grid
            div.span8 Level 1 column
              div.row.show-grid
                div.span5 Level 2
                div.span3 Level 2
          pre.prettyprint.
            | &lt;div class="row"&gt;
            | &lt;div class="span9"&gt;
            | Level 1 column
            | &lt;div class="row"&gt;
            | &lt;div class="span6"&gt;Level 2&lt;/div&gt;
            | &lt;div class="span3"&gt;Level 2&lt;/div&gt;
            | &lt;/div&gt;
            | &lt;/div&gt;
            | &lt;/div&gt;

        section#fluidGridSystem
          div.page-header
            h1 Fluid grid system

          h2 Live fluid grid example
          p The fluid grid system uses percents instead of pixels for column
            | widths. It has the same responsive capabilities as our fixed
            | grid system, ensuring proper proportions for key screen
            | resolutions and devices.
          div.bs-docs-grid
            div.row-fluid.show-grid
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
              div.span1 1
            div.row-fluid.show-grid
              div.span4 4
              div.span4 4
              div.span4 4
            div.row-fluid.show-grid
              div.span4 4
              div.span8 8
            div.row-fluid.show-grid
              div.span6 6
              div.span6 6
            div.row-fluid.show-grid
              div.span12 12

          h2 Basic fluid grid HTML
          p Make any row "fluid" by changing <code>.row</code> to <code>.row-fluid</code>. The column classes stay the exact same, making it easy to flip between fixed and fluid grids.
          pre.prettyprint.
            | &lt;div class="row-fluid"&gt;
            |   &lt;div class="span4"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
            |   &lt;div class="span8"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
            | &lt;/div&gt;

          h2 Fluid offsetting
          p Operates the same way as the fixed grid system offsetting: add <code>.offset*</code> to any column to offset by that many columns.
          div.bs-docs-grid
            div.row-fluid.show-grid
              div.span4.4
              div.span4.offset4 4 offset 4
            div.row-fluid.show-grid
              div.span3.offset3 3 offset 3
              div.span3.offset3 3 offset 3
            div.row-fluid.show-grid
              div.span6.offset6 6 offset 6
          pre.prettyprint.
            | &lt;div class="row-fluid"&gt;
            |   &lt;div class="span4"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
            |   &lt;div class="span4 offset2"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
            | &lt;/div&gt;
          h2 Fluid nesting
          p Fluid grids utilize nesting differently: each nested level
            | of columns should add up to 12 columns. This is because the
            | fluid grid uses percentages, not pixels, for setting widths.
          div.row-fluid.show-grid
            div.span12 Fluid 12
              div.row-fluid.show-grid
                div.span6 Fluid 6
                  div.row-fluid.show-grid
                    div.span6 Fluid 6
                    div.span6 Fluid 6
                div.span6 Fluid 6
          pre.prettyprint.
            | &lt;div class="row-fluid"&gt;
            |   &lt;div class="span12"&gt;
            |     Fluid 12
            |     &lt;div class="row-fluid"&gt;
            |       &lt;div class="span6"&gt;
            |         Fluid 6
            |         &lt;div class="row-fluid"&gt;
            |           &lt;div class="span6"&gt;Fluid 6&lt;/div&gt;
            |           &lt;div class="span6"&gt;Fluid 6&lt;/div&gt;
            |         &lt;/div&gt;
            |       &lt;/div&gt;
            |       &lt;div class="span6"&gt;Fluid 6&lt;/div&gt;
            |     &lt;/div&gt;
            |   &lt;/div&gt;
            | &lt;/div&gt;

